message: Welcome to the crafting game! Here's what I've learned: 1. Always use 'scissors' on 'soft' ingredients (both artificial and natural). This consistently creates 'cut' items with a value of 25. 2. NEVER use 'scissors' on 'hard' ingredients (natural or artificial), as it results in negative values. 3. Combining two 'cut' items is good. If you combine a 'cut artificial soft' item with a 'cut natural soft' item, you can get a high value of 80. 4. Combining *three or more* items will result in a negative 'overcomplicated' item, so stick to two components for collages. 5. The 'frame' tool seems less effective; it yields 20 for 'framed sunflower', but don't try to use 'scissors' on a framed item, it ruins it! Focus on 'soft' ingredients with 'scissors' and two-component combinations for best results. Good luck!
